{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1939 |Team=Oregon State Beavers |Image= |ImageSize=200px |Conference=Pacific Coast Conference |ShortConference=PCC |APRank= |CoachRank= |Record=9-1-1 |ConfRecord=6-1-1 |HeadCoach=[[Lon Stiner]] |StadiumArena=[[Bell Field]] |Champion= Pineapple Bowl Champions |BowlTourney= [[1940 Pineapple Bowl|Pineapple Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult= W 39-6 vs. Hawaii }} {{1939 PCC football standings}} The '''1939 Oregon State Beavers football team''' represented [[Oregon State University|Oregon State College]] in the [[1939 college football season|1939 NCAA college football season]]. The Beavers ended this season with nine wins, one loss, and one tie. The Beavers scored 186 points and allowed 77 points. Oregon State won the inaugural Pineapple Bowl, 39-6. The team was led by head coach Lon Stiner.
==Schedule== The Beavers finished the season with an 9&ndash;1&ndash;1 record, 6&ndash;1&ndash;1 in the Pacific Coast Conference. Ranks are based on the time the game was played.
